description:
Loklok are sticks of meat, egg and vegetables which you can find at night in Johor â€“ our favourite weekend getaway (oh JB please let us visit soon â€“ need a massage badly besides your awesome awesome food). These stick skewers are usually sold in a food truck and commonly found near pubs and night establishments.
There are 2 ways you can choose your lok lok to be done â€“ boiling or deep-frying
Boiling â€“ Customers usually dip their food of choice in a stick in boiling water of a common pot and let it cook
Deep-frying â€“ Customers usually pass their food to the vendor who would deep fry it for them
So after eating all your food, you wave for the vendor to count (different skewers different price â€“ most are colour coded) and you pay! Depending on the item, such sticks normally costs around RM1.50 to RM6. Food can range from vegetables like mushrooms and long beans to tofu skin, pork belly, cheese tofu, salmon, smoked duck, also our favourite â€“ quail eggs and century eggs!
After which you choose your own dip at the dip station which consists of thai chilli sauce, garlic chilli and satay sauce
Hope we can visit JB soon!

description:
A BIG THANKS to Sophia and the team at @thegoodburgersg for sending over this burgerlicious feast! ğŸ”ğŸ” .
The Goodburger food truck was established a year ago and serves up burgers based on the plant-based ImpossibleÂ burger patties. Being animal lovers, they focus on sustainability and being kinder to the world, hence specialising in these meatless burgers. You must be wondering: a yummy meatless burger.. impossible, right? Yes. IMPOSSIBLEÂ is truly the answer! ğŸ˜‰ .
Iâ€™ve tried meatless burgers before and am not a fan so I kept my expectations low for this. Took my first bite and WOW! Very impressive! The patties tasted very similar to meat patties and not only that, it was actually really delicious! Tried both the Double Classic (classic cheeseburger with double patties) and the Black Tie (posher burger with truffle aioli). It was a tough choice but my personal favourite is the Double Classic. The sauce they use is absolutely fantastic (they call it the TGB secret sauce) and this is what makes the burger so darn good! On the sides, their onion rings are pretty good as they were the tempura style battered rings which remained very light, fluffy and crispy despite being a delivery order. The churros were also yummy and was a good sweet ending to a yummy meal.
.
I canâ€™t wait to try their other offerings but 1 step at a time, because I want another Classic with that TGB secret sauce for sure! My suggestion? Go and try their Classic first and see what you think of that secret sauce (come tell me if you figure out whatâ€™s in that sauce!). ğŸ˜
.
They deliver! Check them out on their IG or atÂ thegoodburger.sgÂ or better yet, if you want it fresh off the grill then head over to Coronation Plaza at Bukit Timah. The Goodburger: some may say they make good burgers. But I say they make great burgers ğŸ‘ğŸ»

description:
This is a takeaway meal that I would have kicked myself for missing. Because this is really, by far, the best hokkien mee weâ€™ve ever had. And a beautiful meal altogether.

Chef @jemm_cooks, owner of @lebinchotan, set up a new business label called @zhen_de_la, for his CB takeaway menu. It offers four izakaya type items: bite-sized chicken, a very spicy lala soup, his signature hokkien mee, and his very spicy jar of chilli.

The chicken bites was the first dish we all reached for, and very moreish they were indeed. Marinated in sake amongst other secret ingredients, once you start, you canâ€™t stop. I had already a chicken dish prepped at home, but very glad I was that I decided to still pick this up.

The lala soup was a real è¾£å¦¹! This chilli padi of a dish drew all of us in, but one by one, the rest dropped out, cos it was simply too much for them to handle. So, I happily slurped it up all by myself.

But nothing nothing compares to the star of the show - the hokkien mee. It was a literal ocean of prawn, squid goodness accentuated by generous crispy bits of fried lard. I ordered two boxes - one of prawns only, and one with scallops. Skip the scallops - they dun travel well, but definitely YES to the prawns. The seafood were huge, plump and scrumptious. Coupled with the noodles swimming and soaking up all that sea-tasty yumminess, every mouthful is an exhilarating explosion of flavours and satisfaction.

If you havenâ€™t tried @zhen_de_laâ€™s yummy offerings, this could be your last chance. With Phase 2 opening tomorrow, Chef @jemm_cooks has said that the chilli will stay, but the noodles may go. You can whatsapp your order to him at 87213939.

description:
#Repost @foodiejerm
â€¢ â€¢ â€¢ â€¢ â€¢ â€¢
Ratu Lemper

A BIG THANKS to Carol from @RatuLemper for sending over these delicious treats! If you didn't already know, the Lemper is a delicious snack originating from Indonesia made of glutinous rice filled with savoury chicken, meat or fish, then wrapped inside a banana leaf. "Ratu" means queen and after tasting these, you will have no doubt why they are called the Queen of Lemper!
. 
The generous care pack came with an assortment of different flavoured Lemper: Spicy Chicken, Beef Rendang, Mutton Satay and Tuna. They were all nicely packed and each piece had its banana leaf neatly folded and tucked. They look really pretty but bite into one and you will see the Queen means business! The rice is cooked just right and each piece had just the right balance of rice and filling. The fillings were really tasty! They were all very good but my personal favourite will have to be the Beef Rendang..or the Mutton Satay? or maybe the Spicy Chicken (their best seller). You know what? All 3 of these were seriously good and I could not decide which was best! If you try them, let me know what you think ğŸ˜‰
.
The assortment of colourful kueh included Bika Ambon, Putri Salat, Kue Bakar Pandan, Kaswi Kaya, and Kue Koswi. These were adorably colourful but the choice for a favourite was clear. The Bika Ambon! Fantastic texture and wonderfully fragrant, each bite of this was pure bliss! It was definitely a great dessert after chomping down on the various savoury Lemper.
. 
They take their food seriously and their motto is to serve to customers only the things they would serve their own kids and loved ones. With this, one can see the difference in taste, quality and freshness in their products (all freshly handmade daily with no artificial flavouring or preservatives).Â All products are Halal. .
.
.
.
. .
.

@laut.singapore 
Itâ€™s time to celebrate as we come to an end to phase 1 of the circuit breaker and welcome phase 2! And why not celebrate with good food and drinks @laut.singapore !
Yes! This new gastrobar will be open itâ€™s door for dinner this Friday!
ğŸ”»
In the mean time, takeaway and delivery is still available and you can head on down to their website to place your orders! Complimentary island-wide delivery when you order a minimum of S$50.

Inspired by the culture and produce of Southeast Asia, @laut.singapore menu is indeed a fusion of sorts taking traditional recipes and reinventing them and giving them a â€˜Lautâ€™ twist! Here are some of the items I tried.
â–«ï¸Thunder Tea Rice
This â€˜Risottoâ€™ is one of the best Iâ€™ve tried! Itâ€™s creamy, tasty and comes with a host of familiar SEA ingredients like Thunder Tea Butter, Century Eggs, Petai and 3 huge King Prawns!
â–«ï¸Laut Curry
This curry/ broth is so addictive that i couldnâ€™t stop sipping away! Plus itâ€™s loaded with ingredients like Seabass, Shellfish, Seasonal Greens, Rendang Broth! Itâ€™s indeed a summary of what @laut.singapore represents!
â–«ï¸Burnt Eggplant Dip
This is highly addictive! Fresh crispy Curry Spiced Papadums and accompanied with Burnt Eggplant dip that is consist of Chickpeas, Tomato & Onion Relishâ ! Sooooo good
â–«ï¸Cocktails 
Do check out their bespoke cocktails which are available for delivery too! All the flavors are mostly ASEAN inspired and you are definitely gonna get some kick sipping them!ğŸ˜‡

This looks messy but the crunchy nachos and grilled meats with, cheese, soft black beans, fresh salsa, and guacamole make a wonderful treat. The downside though...been some 2 months since I had Mexican and so my tummy didnâ€™t quite agree with the food lol. Nevertheless I enjoyed it greatly and wanna have more. Their nachos is really the best in town and drizzled with their spicy sauce, itâ€™s really the bomb! .

When the day feels long, or I feel extra tired, I like to eat simply and look for easy quick-fix meals. Vietnamese rice wraps often comes to mind, for its ease and fuss-free nature, and the fact that I can plump it full of vegetables. It was fun to make and quick to eat, as Son wolfed down four in a go. I put boiled prawns, crabstick, roast chicken slices, ricotta, carrot sticks, cucumber sticks and even salad leaves. I was even prepared to try some kimchi inside, but Son said â€œnoâ€, so had to contain my curiosity on that one. Maybe, next time!

description:
Beetroot Walnut Pasta with Pan-Fried Codfish for dinner. Beetroot is so nutritious but it is so tough to eat or drink on its own. I usually use beetroot to get its beautiful natural red colouring. I love homemade pasta sauce. Tonight, I turned beetroot into squash and create beetroot pasta sauce.

Stir fry garlic and onion with butter and pour blended beetroot squash, cooking cream, coarse black pepper, coriander and a cup of lemon juice. Mix the cooked pasta into cooked pasta sauce and serve with crushed walnuts and fresh coriander. ğŸ˜‹ğŸ˜‹

A BIG THANKS to the incredible team at @littlebrownieandfriends for sending over this delightful package of lovingly made brownies and muffins! ğŸ˜Š
.
"Out of the batters, we rise.." says Little Brownie and rise to the occasion they did indeed! It was rather difficult to decide a favourite when faced with so many options.. ğŸ¤”ğŸ¤·ğŸ»â€â™‚ï¸ .
Their brownies come in a wide variety of flavours aside from the classic original and this includes ovomaltine, oreo, s'mores, nutella, PBJ, peanut butter and speculoos.. That's a lot to choose from! Personally I thought the original and ovomaltine were the best (try them and tell me what you think!). Then they have blondies! Dark choco, white choco, kaya, kinder bueno, kit kat and red bean just to name a few.. In fact, I think if you have any special requests, reach out to Little Brownie and I'm sure they will fix your cravings! ğŸ˜‰ .
Don't forget the yummy muffins! Crumble Muffins to be exact! This comes in apple, blueberry, and banana walnut. My pick? The blueberry (biased, being a blueberry fan) ğŸ˜¬
.
Check them out and see what your favourite is.. I now know I'm a muffin guy! Or am I a brownie guy? Hhhmmm.. Like I said, choosing is tough... ğŸ˜ .

In the midst of the Circuit Breaker period, @laifabar started a fundraising campaign for the seniors at Lions Befrienders. Most of these elders do not have anyone to care for them and are no longer able to provide for themselves. The COVID-19 situation only made things even harder due to a lack of volunteers and sponsors. In this initiative, aptly named â€œLai Fa Caresâ€, nutritious meals were delivered to the doorsteps of the seniors to ensure they did not have to worry about their next meal. Such people are truly a blessing to this community, going out of their way to help others in need. Letâ€™s continue to support one another through this difficult period. How can you bless someone in need today?

description:
Dinner last night was like a dream. Cos it was dinner from @thesushibar_sg. In fact, every time we dine with @thesushibar_sg, we always come out feeling well-fed, well-loved and definitely, absolutely satisfied. It was our regular weekend fix, till CB put a stop to it.

I was elated to find they have a takeaway menu for CB and have ordered from @thesushibar_sg once. At that time, the hamachi was not on the menu. And when I asked, was told that they only have the collar available. But we wanted the whole head, so we passed.

Yesterday, we were missing our @thesushibar_sg fix, so I checked again and yessssss, they have the hamachi kama - head and collar! Whatâ€™s more, it was on a lovely promotional price of S$18.90. And with takeaways on Monday being 20%off the total bill, it was a very nice deal indeed.

I ordered two in the end, because our growing boys love it as well and have become discerning hamachi eaters, always asking for cheek meat! Also tried out the promotional truffle pork cheek don, which was absolutely scrumptious. Finally, that salmon kabuto miso soup for 2-3pax for under S$10 - I would be insane not to try it.

Other than the hamachi, the other two were new dishes to us. And happily, everything was delicious. In true @thesushibar_sg style, portions were more than huge, and with the very decent prices, especially with the promotions, gave lots of bang for the buck.

We supplemented the meal with hubsâ€™s own crabmeat fried rice, back by popular demand, and with the ikura and tobiko I purposely bought for the kids. This is their idea of a happy meal. As a result, there is one hamachi left, and this will go towards our next lunch or dinner.

Happy Meal indeed!

â€œUni Moriawase - Donâ€ by @kishosg ! Perhaps the most decadent and crazy request Iâ€™ve made thus far. Uni Season is upon us, the best, the incredibles, are curated, transacted and savoured. @chef_kazu_hamamoto the de facto Uni connoisseur and monger, lands some of the best varieties from Japan. I said, â€œKazu, letâ€™s make a Uni-Don, featuring the best of what you got....â€. Days later, this was what I got. Kazu splashed out 4 Murasaki, 3 Aka and 3 Bahun, insane! 10 types, different undertones, varying creaminess and some surprises. Like what @abbey_thebolobao said ,â€ it was like a Uni-classâ€. For those Uni-lovers, this is the box to get. You ainâ€™t going to get this when we dine-in. 
The types of Uni i had-
*******
Murasaki (Top Row from R to L)
1. Ensui - Yoichi Hokkaido
2. Daizen - Aomori Prefecture
3. Higashizawa - Hakodate Hokkaido
4. Hirono (4 years) - Iwate Prefecture
*******
Bahun (Bottom Row R to L)
5. Ensui - Yoichi Hokkaido
6. Ogawa - Rebun Island
7. Ogawa - Nemuro Hokkaido
*******
Aka (Bottom Row from Ogawa)
8. Saga Karatsu
9. Nagasaki
10. Hagi - Yamaguchi
*******
Fantastic Uni-cation. Thank you for the crazy effort Kazu! #noneedmeepok #fightcovid19 â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”

1) Buddha Jumps over the Wall Rice Dumpling ($48), a luxurious parcel wrapped with fragrant pandan leaves around a trove of decadent ingredients such as South African Abalone, Japanese Sea Cucumber, Sakura Ebi and Japanese Dried Scallops.

2) Specialty Yunnan Rose Red Bean Dumpling ($18 for 3), which draws on Chef Leungâ€™s expertise in innovative regional ingredients. Who else needs to cancel the Japan trip this year? 
Fret not, you can still enjoy authentic Japanese food from Panko Pocket just like @alleatsbigandsmall ğŸ˜‹ğŸ˜‹ğŸ˜‹
-
-
-

#repost @alleatsbigandsmall â€œMummy, when can we go Japan again? I miss Japan. I want to go skiing. And this time, Iâ€™ll ski on all fours, like a dog. I think that will make me go faster,â€ the little one asked me today.

I donâ€™t know, dear. I donâ€™t know when we can go Japan. And honestly, I donâ€™t know when we can and will travel again.

But Mummy can do one thing for you. We can still get good Japanese food here.

Mummy discovered a new Japanese street eat today. Itâ€™s Panko Pockets from Osaka, not exactly ski country. But when I saw it today, I noticed its crunchy crust and that itâ€™s best when taken warm. And I saw that itâ€™s either a stew or curry inside with the meat. And I was transported immediately to a wintry Japan, and I could totally see myself all wrapped up, walking the famed food streets of Osaka, enjoying this hot and satisfying treat.

So I bought three. And I heated them up in the oven. And I prepared a yummy salad to go with it. And you can hear how crunchy it is in the video attached. And see how lovely it is when cut open in my photos. And finally having tasted it today, donâ€™t you agree that itâ€™s totally got the taste and feel of our much loved and much missed Japan? Missing you much, Nippon!

description:
Wanted to spruce up one of my favorite local dishes. Rainbow mee hoon kueh, handmade with natural food coloring. Accompanied with flavorful mushroom and meatball toppings, in a bowl of piping hot broth.

250g plain flour
100g vegetable*, steamed and pureÌed 
1 large egg
1/2 tsp sugar
1/2 tsp salt
50-70ml water
*Iâ€™m using pumpkin for yellow, beetroot for red and spinach for green. These are optional natural food coloring, you really donâ€™t taste the veg much. You can choose to omit them but do add bit more water to the dough.

On low speed, knead all ingredients in a stand mixer except water.
As the dough come together, add water 1 tbsp at a time and increase to medium speed.
Stop adding water when the dough pulls clean from the side and is soft and pliable. Dough should not be hard. 
If dough is too wet, add flour 1 tbsp at a time.
Cover dough in a greased bowl and leave to rest for 1hr.
Pinch bite sized portion of dough, flatten with thumb and cook in boiling water. Noodle is ready when it floats.

Braised mushroom topping:
Fry 2 cloves garlic slices and 1 slice of ginger till fragrant. Add in sliced and soaked mushroom (50g dried), stir fry for couple minutes. Add in 11/2 tbsp oyster sauce, 1/2 tsp dark sauce, 1/2 tsp brown sugar, 100ml water. Bring to boil, then let simmer over v low heat and covered for at least an hour.

Minced meat topping:
Marinate 180g minced pork with 1 tsp sesame oil, 11/2 tsp soy sauce, 1/2 tsp salt, 1/2 sugar, few dash of pepper and lastly 1 tsp of cornflour. Spoon into small balls and cook in broth.

Broth:
Ikan bilis and pork ribs. No need to add salt. Cooking the minced meat in the broth will add enough flavor to the broth.
